The samples on scavenging DPPH free-radical was studied using the modified method described by Guo49. Briefly, twelve microliters of pectin solutions were incubated with 0.1 mM DPPH in anhydrous ethanol (188 μL) in a 96-well micro plate plates. The reaction mixture reacted at room temperature for 30 min. The absorbance of the sample solutions were determined at 517 nm. The DPPH activity was calculated by the following equation:5Scavengingeffect(%)=(1−Asample517/Acontrol517)×100\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
